Dawn French, 64, looked chic as she rocked a grey quiff at the Sondheim's Old Friends event on Tuesday evening. The French and Saunders actress and comedian showcased her cropped grey hair at the gala. She opted for a change during lockdown, when she stopped wearing her hair in her iconic bob style. Dawn wore an all-black outfit for the occassion, as did many other attendees. Her outfit included a flowing leather jacket and a black jersey dress with a V-neck. The Sondheim's Old Friends event was held in aid of the Stephen Sondheim Foundation. The event was a tribute to the legendary composer and lyricist, who died in November 2021. 